Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.14,0:02:17.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This the famous 1000-step stairway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.68,0:02:19.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like a fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.69,0:02:20.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Shichika.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.90,0:02:22.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai is at the summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.44,0:02:26.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to walk yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.69,0:02:30.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I did cross that hellish Inaba desert on my own feet you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.82,0:02:32.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like this is nothing in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.33,0:02:42.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait Shichika...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.67,0:02:43.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.88,0:02:45.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.75,0:02:46.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.71,0:02:50.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been traveling with me for three months already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.22,0:02:52.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you figured out how weak I am by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.84,0:02:54.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Figured out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.18,0:02:56.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A gust of wind would blow me over, and drizzles of rain put me to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.90,0:03:00.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I pushed this weak body all the way up here on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.60,0:03:02.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say that's worthy of praise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.11,0:03:04.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.27,0:03:05.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.11,0:03:07.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to carry you then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:10.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I could subject myself to something so disgraceful?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.70,0:03:11.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Disgraceful?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.61,0:03:15.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'd be clinging onto a man from behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.53,0:03:16.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.62,0:03:18.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"So what"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.12,0:03:20.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Our b-bodies would be in close contact!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.33,0:03:22.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.54,0:03:24.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a piggyback then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.10,0:03:26.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerio!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.09,0:03:30.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A piggyback would be way too embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.47,0:03:32.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not something a grown man and woman would do!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:35.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But back on the island, Nee-chan and I often—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:36.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Often"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.81,0:03:40.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.85,0:03:43.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you want to do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.31,0:03:46.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot, I'm a strategian.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.16,0:03:49.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I have a plan for something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:50.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.86,0:03:52.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this good?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:55.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This way it won't be embarrassing even if someone sees us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.41,0:04:01.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Togame...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:02.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.87,0:04:06.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This Sentou Tsurugi sword... are there really a thousand of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.92,0:04:08.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.04,0:04:12.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The main focus of Tsurugi is overwhelming numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.51,0:04:14.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hence, a thousand swords in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:17.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk about them like they're carrots or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.55,0:04:19.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.93,0:04:22.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The final gate is in view now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.98,0:04:26.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured it'd already be dusk when we arrived, given how slowly you walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.85,0:04:28.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:51.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:57.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Orders from the Shogunate?{maybe: So you're from the Shogunate, then.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:04:59.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.26,0:05:02.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, that'll make it more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:03.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Miss Strategian.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.77,0:05:09.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really Tsuruga Meisai?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.81,0:05:11.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't look like a former mountain bandit to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.73,0:05:15.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My time as a bandit ended seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.74,0:05:19.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've since washed my hands of the business and haven't met my compatriots since.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.66,0:05:24.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Tsuruga Meisai was the name of the previous priest here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:27.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and I merely took up that name for the sake of convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.33,0:05:32.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus it's hard to answer if I'm "really" Tsuruga Meisai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:34.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My old name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.92,0:05:36.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've forgotten it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.47,0:05:38.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I had one to start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.59,0:05:40.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Bandits don't need a name, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.43,0:05:43.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's called a shrine, but that's just how it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.97,0:05:46.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one but shrine maidens here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.06,0:05:49.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of like what Buddhists would call a convent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.31,0:05:52.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen our shrine maidens, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.11,0:05:54.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the ones down below right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.82,0:05:58.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just below. They're here in the main shrine too, about 50 of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.16,0:06:01.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is officially an armed shrine after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.91,0:06:08.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We have 1000 shrine maidens, so if we don't spread them around, this area would overflow with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.72,0:06:13.25,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So, since you're here on orders from the Shogunate, you must have some urgent business.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.63,0:06:19.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,About that, Meisai-dono, can I speak with you privately?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.63,0:06:20.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.26,0:06:22.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Togame...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.14,0:06:23.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.93,0:06:25.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Go play outside for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.27,0:06:29.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hear you out in the main shrine then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.48,0:06:35.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The 50 shrine maidens in this area all very unsettled, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:42.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Some killed their parents, some killed their families, some wiped out their entire clan...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.53,0:06:45.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They are all devoid of inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:47.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't mind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.37,0:06:53.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As a side note, you have quite interesting hair, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.29,0:06:58.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not young enough to be called "young lady" by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:07:01.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,From my perspective you're a young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:04.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, it does seem that you're not as young as you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.26,0:07:08.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai-dono...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:11.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now now, no need to rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:25.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:32.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, it's not poisoned. {Togame would fail the Princess Bride test}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.71,0:07:40.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You drink well!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.88,0:07:41.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:43.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.26,0:07:45.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.59,0:07:49.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, to tell you the truth, I'm pretty sure I know what you're here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:52.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about Shikizaki Kiki's Deviant Blades, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.31,0:07:56.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The higher-ups have only ever meddled in our affairs once before, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.23,0:08:01.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes without saying, but I mean General Kyuu's sword-hunt decree.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:05.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you say you're the army general director.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:10.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So in all likelihood, you're here about Sentou Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.08,0:08:16.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As you have guessed, my duty is to collect Shikizaki Kiki's perfected Deviant Blades.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:17.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,To what end?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:20.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,To maintain public peace and order, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:25.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already obtained two of the swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.76,0:08:29.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Zettou Kanna and Zantou Namakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:33.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As the owner of Sentou Tsurugi, you must at least know their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.44,0:08:36.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:40.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've already managed to collect two of the swords that General Kyuu could not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.94,0:08:41.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:45.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And your Sentou Tsurugi will be the third.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.45,0:08:51.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The only swords which Shikizaki considered disposable, the ultimate and absolute 1000 blades —
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.66,0:08:56.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentou Tsurugi, the swords you have your 1000 shrine maidens armed with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.63,0:09:03.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from the Shogunate, so I'm well aware of the situation that Izumo is in,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.21,0:09:06.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,including the circumstances of the Sanzu shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.76,0:09:12.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were to hand Sentou over, the Shogunate would be happy to take care of those "circumstances".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.14,0:09:16.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this is a bad deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:18.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.06,0:09:19.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I do think it's a good offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.65,0:09:21.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.36,0:09:24.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,there's one thing I'd like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.91,0:09:35.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.29,0:09:42.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I do something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.47,0:09:52.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that boy there your man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.76,0:09:54.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.02,0:09:56.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Your sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.93,0:10:00.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like he's carrying one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.10,0:10:01.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he hiding it somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.81,0:10:03.32,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:06.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Its name is Yasuri Shichika.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.03,0:10:08.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The 7th generation Kyotouryuu head, Yasuri Shichika.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.24,0:10:14.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The 7th generation Kyotouryuu head, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.95,0:10:18.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, that's why you called him your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.04,0:10:20.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He can be a little too sharp sometimes though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.71,0:10:24.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you kill the previous owners of Kanna and Namakura with that sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:25.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.42,0:10:28.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The hero of the rebellion, Kyotouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.30,0:10:30.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Swordsmen who use no swords...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.14,0:10:32.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.89,0:10:35.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No... it's exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:42.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If my Sentouryuu were to be pitted against that boy's Kyotouryuu, which would win?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:42.19,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Sentouryuu - Thousand Blade Style
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.19,0:10:43.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentouryuu?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.81,0:10:45.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I've decided, young lady—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.77,0:10:48.32,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Togame the strategian.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:52.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my decision as the head of the Sanzu shrine of Daisen, Izumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.62,0:10:56.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I am willing to hand over Sentou Tsurugi,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.33,0:10:59.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,as long as you accept some minor conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.17,0:11:09.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.72,0:11:13.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.51,0:11:15.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,it turned out for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.36,0:11:20.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to find the first blade of Sentou Tsurugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:25.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Tsurugi is 1000 identical swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:30.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai says that an original, the first sword, exists amongst them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:31.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And you have to find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:34.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Without your help, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:42.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I find the first sword and you win in a one-on-one fight with Meisai, she'll give us Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.06,0:11:43.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.35,0:11:45.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We give her Kanna and Namakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.94,0:11:47.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:48.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.18,0:11:49.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.86,0:11:53.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we win we only get one sword, but if shes wins she gets two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.23,0:11:54.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.24,0:11:58.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I wanted to avoid fighting this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:00.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shichika, you can let go of my hair now—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:09.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:11.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.50,0:12:15.25,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Would this be that "disgrace" thing you were talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:18.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerio!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:20.64,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't dodge me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.64,0:12:22.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really dodging you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.93,0:12:25.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hear your excuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:29.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that Togame-dono has accepted your conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.43,0:12:37.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two aren't just master and servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.94,0:12:40.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, they aren't just a couple either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.46,0:12:43.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They are most likely tied together by fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.75,0:12:47.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.62,0:12:49.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see that hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.47,0:12:54.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hair doesn't get like that unless something significant happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.12,0:12:55.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And the way she acts...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.35,0:13:01.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that no matter what cruelties one suffers through, one's true self cannot simply be discarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.65,0:13:02.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.07,0:13:07.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It may be an inherent desire to protect oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:09.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.91,0:13:13.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would she wear such brightly colored clothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.87,0:13:17.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So she does not forget herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.23,0:13:21.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing that Strategian is the daughter of some feudal lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.09,0:13:25.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If things had turned out better, she might have been the princess of her own country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.55,0:13:31.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither a world of war nor a world of peace can sooth our pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.49,0:13:45.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Shichika?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.86,0:13:49.64,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it suit me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.99,0:13:52.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How does it strike you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:13:58.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have bothered asking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.67,0:14:05.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, if I ask you "Does this suit me?" you must reply "It suits you well."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.38,0:14:13.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, Shichika didn't have what we call "Miko moe" today.{check need a note? shorten to Miko-Moe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.83,0:14:16.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Togame, where are you going today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.10,0:14:20.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,First I'm going to inspect those black shrine maidens' swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.23,0:14:21.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,After that I'll be down below.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.86,0:14:26.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm ready to come back tonight, I'll light a torch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:29.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Come down to meet me when you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:32.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is that the only role I have in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.03,0:14:33.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:34.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:36.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't wander around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.40,0:14:44.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:52.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Poison of the sword, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.92,0:15:04.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey little lady, wanna play with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.57,0:15:05.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:06.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.45,0:15:16.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The one in the way is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.77,0:15:23.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.13,0:15:24.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll kill your ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:41.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Woah, I've never seen a sword like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.79,0:15:45.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see a path to the heavens opening up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.44,0:15:47.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A sword is not for display.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:49.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It is for killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:52.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have you fall for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.91,0:16:03.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.30,0:16:17.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the remaining Sentou within the shrine grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.78,0:16:54.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai-dono!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:56.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.30,0:16:57.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Get them out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.72,0:16:58.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:16:59.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.10,0:17:06.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai-dono!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.73,0:17:07.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.83,0:17:30.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.75,0:17:33.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:35.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.67,0:17:37.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, get your wounds tended to!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.84,0:17:39.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.97,0:17:43.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Put the swords back on the table when you're done inspecting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.47,0:17:44.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai-dono!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.44,0:17:47.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.41,0:18:03.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When I find the original sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:04.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai will be...{killed by Shichika :<}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.10,0:18:19.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that Maniwa Koumori and Maniwa Shirasagi failed to obtain Shikizaki Kiki's Deviant Blades and met their fate...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:24.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Koumori already had Kanna though... I wonder what could have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:28.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It bothers me, it bothers me, it bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.70,0:18:30.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:37.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.55,0:18:43.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Master, w-we've arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.18,0:18:49.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When people put so much faith in me, I have to live up to those expectations!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.14,0:18:52.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.19,0:18:54.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ninpou: Uzugatana!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.19,0:18:54.57,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Uzugatana - Whirlpool Blade
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.57,0:18:59.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is why they call me Kuizame of Sabaku — written 'chain' and 'bind'.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.94,0:19:03.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have made an appearance last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.99,0:19:05.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You people say some funny things!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:10.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Cutting down people like you is the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:20.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun, I'm happy I was able to answer their expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.05,0:19:23.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, time to get to work and collect Sentou Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.26,0:19:26.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It was located at the Sanzu shrine, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.93,0:19:29.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to it, I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.57,0:20:29.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shichika-dono.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.37,0:20:30.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.20,0:20:33.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, I was free anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.79,0:20:39.25,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time those maidens have had contact with anyone besides myself and Meisai-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:43.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Meisai bring them here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:47.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, most of them were serving here under the previous priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:53.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, there are some who heard the rumors of Meisai-sama and struggled to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.47,0:20:54.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumors of Meisai?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:57.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That she had swords which sooth the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:20:59.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be Tsurugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.52,0:21:04.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.03,0:21:09.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel that aura that Shikizaki swords have from your swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:12.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I could be wrong though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:14.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:20.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't feel like Shikizaki swords to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:22.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He says some interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.84,0:21:26.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I must have a talk with that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.05,0:21:32.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Togame sure is taking her time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.85,0:21:36.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyotouryuu boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.19,0:21:39.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Want some?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.36,0:21:46.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you helped our maidens out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.44,0:21:47.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You have my thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.61,0:21:49.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.20,0:21:52.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, what kind of shrine is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.79,0:21:54.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The maidens run away as soon as they see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.99,0:21:56.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.62,0:22:02.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So the young lady hasn't told you anything about the Sanzu shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.08,0:22:04.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.04,0:22:07.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,this shrine is something like a refuge temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.38,0:22:08.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A refuge temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.55,0:22:10.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's sometimes called the shrine of separation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.13,0:22:13.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really get either of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.39,0:22:17.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly are those black shrine maidens?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.98,0:22:21.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you give them swords without wearing one yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.85,0:22:25.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Because those swords are necessary for those girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.73,0:22:28.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, more like a necessary evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.32,0:22:32.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.58,0:22:37.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Their mental health was destroyed after long term abuse by men.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.54,0:22:39.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mental health... destroyed?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.66,0:22:41.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just mentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.92,0:22:45.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Both their souls and bodies have been abused to their limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.38,0:22:48.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, they've been abused beyond their limits,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.92,0:22:52.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,then simply thrown away, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.18,0:22:58.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This shrine's maidens are those abandoned girls who have been picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.77,0:23:01.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You should understand why they fear you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.94,0:23:07.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,To them, that's all men are — something to be feared and avoided.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.77,0:23:10.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear and avoidance between men and women...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.49,0:23:13.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.57,0:23:15.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.16,0:23:18.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is a different world from that of a swordsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:22.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do know why Togame asked me not to wander about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.29,0:23:27.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A very feminine consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:30.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, you should have picked up on another thing —
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.80,0:23:34.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I give the shrine maidens Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.26,0:23:40.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's to use the poison of Shikizaki Kiki's swords as medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.43,0:23:42.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.31,0:23:47.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking too much medicine becomes poisonous, and poison can be used as medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.06,0:23:53.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The swords should serve to help restore their broken minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.78,0:23:58.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, that's only if the Deviant Blades actually do have power beyond human understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.91,0:24:04.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably the first person to use Shikizaki's swords like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.62,0:24:06.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.88,0:24:10.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No one would try to restore life with a killing tool like Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.84,0:24:13.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But it appears to work to a degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.97,0:24:17.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can say that after watching over them for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.97,0:24:25.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you take away the poison, by obtaining the strength a sword provides, a woman can become equal with men.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:28.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that talisman on their faces the same kind of thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.73,0:24:32.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's simply for coverup.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.53,0:24:37.32,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many among them who've been branded as criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.32,0:24:38.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.62,0:24:42.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's those "circumstances" the little lady talked about before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.04,0:24:44.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It helps make the shrine seem threatening.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.96,0:24:45.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.71,0:24:48.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The talismans are just a mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.83,0:24:51.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's really needed is the sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.29,0:24:55.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't sleep well due to their emotional damage,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.67,0:25:00.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but even with that, carrying Tsurugi with them allows them to retain their sense of self.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.56,0:25:05.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,For them, Sentou Tsurugi is their heart and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.23,0:25:11.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I cannot afford to give up Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.28,0:25:14.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to save as many women as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.48,0:25:20.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can beat you and obtain your two Deviant Blades, I'll have saved another two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.03,0:25:23.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I cannot lose to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.54,0:25:25.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the way it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.25,0:25:30.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I will fight to my utmost, and you'll fight to your utmost.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.13,0:25:32.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be a worthy battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.59,0:25:36.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sympathy tactic, failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.55,0:25:39.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.18,0:25:41.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something important to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.80,0:25:42.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.19,0:25:52.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this bitter drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.11,0:25:55.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're a lightweight, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.03,0:25:56.32,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it was sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.32,0:25:58.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never had it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.44,0:26:00.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.62,0:26:07.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Though contrary to how you look, you can say some pretty harsh things.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.08,0:26:10.25,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not much fun.{Old: Almost like you're heartless.}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.75,0:26:12.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I'm a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.83,0:26:16.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My body and soul don't move for anyone but Togame.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.05,0:26:24.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay with robbing Tsurugi, even though the hearts of these women will break once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.35,0:26:27.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good or bad, I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.02,0:26:31.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If Togame says she wants Tsurugi, then that's absolute for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.27,0:26:33.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do nothing but make you give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.52,0:26:36.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have any doubts about it? {maybe: you don't know inner conflict... do you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.61,0:26:39.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've decided, that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.90,0:26:43.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you just being too lazy to worry about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.78,0:26:46.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Too scared to make a decision yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.91,0:26:49.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Always just "a hassle"?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.75,0:26:53.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't deny I find it a hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.46,0:26:55.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How many people have you killed so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.59,0:26:56.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.71,0:26:58.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Two huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.38,0:27:01.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not many for a person like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.84,0:27:04.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a monkey who grew up on an uninhabited island.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.30,0:27:07.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My first real fight was about two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.47,0:27:10.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So, two people for two Deviant Blades.{のに is expressing 'in order to' not 'omg only two' in this sentence}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.68,0:27:12.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.81,0:27:14.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you kill me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.02,0:27:15.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.56,0:27:17.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Same for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.36,0:27:19.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,how many have you killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.53,0:27:21.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Too many to count.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.11,0:27:23.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only say for certain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.36,0:27:25.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,at least 43.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.95,0:27:27.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,43?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.41,0:27:29.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of number is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.04,0:27:33.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the number of my compatriots I killed when I left the bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.84,0:27:36.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the only kills I'll never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.76,0:27:42.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And conversely, those 43 people are the only ones I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.67,0:27:46.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,People must say I'm a cold-blooded barbarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.60,0:27:51.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But even a person like me needs the resolution to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.60,0:27:53.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Something you're prepared to throw away.{Norg: check - think this is better wording?}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.89,0:27:56.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like you don't have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.23,0:27:58.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.40,0:28:00.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what on earth do you fight for?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.86,0:28:03.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you earlier — for Togame.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.86,0:28:06.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I fell for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.20,0:28:07.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I need any other reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.33,0:28:11.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Throwing-off-balance tactic also failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.45,0:28:12.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.58,0:28:17.25,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, that's not right...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.96,0:28:18.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What isn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.38,0:28:22.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not two people, it's three.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.18,0:28:24.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There was actually one more person.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.60,0:28:28.64,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I slew my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.98,0:28:41.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you noticed me?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.82,0:28:43.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That was faster than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.28,0:28:49.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have liked to have heard just a little more of your interesting discussion.{old: Just a little longer and I would have heard an interesting story, too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.12,0:28:53.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well, thanks to you I've got a good grasp of the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.20,0:28:55.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:59.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose thanking someone after bowing one's head just comes naturally.{Norg: I think this is what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.55,0:29:04.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to introduce myself from a higher position.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.46,0:29:05.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.67,0:29:10.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Announcing myself in the open is good, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.30,0:29:16.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I am one of the 12 heads of the Maniwa corps, Maniwa Kuizame.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.06,0:29:18.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.56,0:29:19.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, a Maniwani...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.61,0:29:22.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Maniwani"?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.15,0:29:26.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good heavens, that is incredibly sublime!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.70,0:29:32.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,To bestow such a lovely name upon a band of ninja assassins such as us,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.24,0:29:35.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,you truly are a benevolent man!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.08,0:29:36.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.33,0:29:40.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't know this particular one, but his group is after the swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.96,0:29:42.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.96,0:29:47.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have traveled here in order to procure the swords you two hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.62,0:29:50.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.18,0:29:52.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The air of hostility is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.35,0:29:55.64,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ninpou Uzugatana!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.81,0:30:03.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is why they call me Sabaku Izame, written 'curse' and 'chain'! {and pronounced desert! <- include this? >.>}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.90,0:30:06.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.15,0:30:10.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to tell me I should have arrived last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.03,0:30:13.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess now's not the time to be saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.87,0:30:14.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.91,0:30:18.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As the head of this shrine that protects Izumo,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.37,0:30:21.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a duty to repel this ninja.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.83,0:30:27.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I know about Kyotouryuu, but you've never seen Sentouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.09,0:30:29.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's unfair right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.34,0:30:30.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.31,0:30:34.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go then.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.27,0:30:40.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good, good, this is exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.41,0:30:56.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, you just asked didn't you, Tsuruga Meisai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.62,0:30:59.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"What on earth do you fight for?"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.41,0:31:01.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were to answer, I'd have to say "for money".
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.87,0:31:06.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm quite proud of the fact that I have never fought for any other reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.25,0:31:07.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.21,0:31:10.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't bother fighting if you have to ask that every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.63,0:31:14.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why do you fight"?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.51,0:31:16.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"For what reason"?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.29,0:31:19.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hear such sloppy questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.02,0:31:20.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.58,0:31:39.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyotouryuu boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.74,0:31:42.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,could you help me deal with this body?{runt -> kid?}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.17,0:31:48.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Slow, slow, slow!!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.92,0:31:52.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been all over this huge shrine — from west to east, south to north,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.30,0:31:54.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,tiring myself running everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.13,0:31:57.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You have some nerve to leisurely nap through it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.64,0:31:57.01,overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,A Maniwani appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.39,0:32:02.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know when another will show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.27,0:32:05.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,so from tomorrow onwards, I'm staying by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.73,0:32:06.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.69,0:32:08.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.94,0:32:11.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the original sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.94,0:32:15.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end it came down to how scratched the sheaths were.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.03,0:32:17.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I can't guarantee it for sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.32,0:32:22.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but the scars on this sheath are the oldest.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.29,0:32:25.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, this sword's most likely the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.29,0:32:27.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.81,0:32:29.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd overlooked the sheath.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.67,0:32:32.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, that helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.17,0:32:35.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.55,0:32:36.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.89,0:32:40.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say it's the original sword then it must be.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.10,0:32:44.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,See you tomorrow then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.60,0:32:46.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,At noon exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.77,0:32:49.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a cup to raise our spirits?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.73,0:32:51.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.25,0:32:53.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyotouryuu boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.36,0:32:57.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,how about we get this over and done with?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.43,0:33:01.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}You're pretty easy going right before a fight with your life on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.97,0:33:04.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That sort of thing's supposed to be my territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.89,0:33:08.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we allow surrender as an option then?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.21,0:33:11.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you feel you can't win, just say you give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.51,0:33:12.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.63,0:33:17.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me your Kyotouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.09,0:33:21.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and you can show me that Sentouryuu you're so proud of.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.86,0:33:22.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Proud?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.36,0:33:26.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not at all proud of Sentouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.57,0:33:29.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This thing is merely a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.95,0:33:33.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.99,0:33:35.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.66,0:33:38.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing will start if we continue this pointless chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.73,0:34:00.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.44,0:34:03.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.58,0:34:11.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wai—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.25,0:34:30.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.92,0:34:32.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ittou: Ichimonji Kiri!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.78,0:34:46.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did she pull that out from anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.25,0:35:09.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So the hunt for the original was just an excuse to bide time for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.93,0:35:11.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is Sentouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.93,0:35:14.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Kyotouryuu boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.18,0:35:18.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't just the use of your opponent's swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.60,0:35:22.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about making all swords on the battlefield your own, hence "Sentouryuu".
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.98,0:35:26.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,With Sentouryuu and Sentou Tsurugi together...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.47,0:35:29.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Chikeikouka: Sentou Meguri!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.47,0:35:29.86,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Chikeikouka = use of the land
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.20,0:35:33.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did those two go?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.62,0:35:36.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to write my report if I don't see the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.95,0:35:41.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyotouryuu is no match for this Sentou Meguri.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.67,0:35:43.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.21,0:35:45.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We did agree surrender is an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.92,0:35:49.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared to let you live if you say you give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.34,0:35:53.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You believe that much in your Sentouryuu?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.02,0:35:54.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.85,0:35:58.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believed in it, from the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.77,0:36:02.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It was everything to me, until that rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.72,0:36:04.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebellion?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.02,0:36:10.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,20 years ago, the rebellion led by Hida Takahito, the lord of Oshuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.82,0:36:19.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My father was the commander of the 2nd squad, 3rd regiment of Izumo's defense corps,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.50,0:36:22.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the master of the Kendo dojo handed down from my ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.62,0:36:26.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He taught me Sentouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.67,0:36:28.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the daughter who was to inherit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.51,0:36:31.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, from a young age,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.94,0:36:36.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I never doubted that Sentouryuu was the ultimate art of defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.47,0:36:42.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, in the midst of battle it was as though Sentouryuu was useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.18,0:36:44.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Father died,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.10,0:36:47.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,along with every one of his disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.39,0:36:51.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the only survivor, as I had never joined the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.28,0:36:54.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost everything in that rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.28,0:36:57.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My house, my family, even my beliefs...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.41,0:37:03.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I realized it, I was using Sentouryuu as a tool for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.96,0:37:08.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not long after, I joined the largest bandit gang in Izumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.34,0:37:12.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Its chief at the time held Sentou Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.80,0:37:19.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentouryuu is an art of absolute self-defense in which you don't arm yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.81,0:37:24.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's founded upon the idea that swords are dispensable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.94,0:37:27.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsurugi follows the same principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.19,0:37:30.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It was no accident that brought Tsurugi to my ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.44,0:37:32.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It was fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.71,0:37:38.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I'd become the bandit chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.53,0:37:43.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My life after that isn't even worth talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.00,0:37:46.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I just fought and killed every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.33,0:37:50.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.00,0:37:52.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have the luxury of thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.21,0:38:02.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I first considered that question when I met Tsuruga Meisai, the priest at the time.{check I have rephrased it..}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.10,0:38:06.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd known about the Sanzu shrine from before,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.52,0:38:10.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,that it was a sanctuary for weak girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.02,0:38:15.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, why didn't they save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.14,0:38:18.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't gods called gods because they help anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.93,0:38:41.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous Tsuruga Meisai said to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.18,0:38:45.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Please, forgive those girls."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.56,0:38:47.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"They've done no wrong."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.69,0:38:50.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were his last words.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.98,0:38:55.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the first time I had heard such words from a dying man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.53,0:38:58.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It made me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.32,0:39:01.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why do I fight?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.57,0:39:04.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why do I live?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.41,0:39:11.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,After returning to the bandit stronghold, I killed my companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.08,0:39:14.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't leave a single one of the 43 alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.88,0:39:18.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, I inherited Tsuruga Meisai's dying wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.76,0:39:24.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've been fighting for those girls ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.10,0:39:26.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I cannot lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.97,0:39:28.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for their sakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.90,0:39:36.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the end of my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.98,0:39:39.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.53,0:39:41.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't continue this useless resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.15,0:39:43.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Admit your defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.70,0:39:46.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyotouryuu cannot match up to Sentouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.41,0:39:48.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the simple truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.63,0:39:59.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I eat the meat of animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.29,0:40:03.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.09,0:40:06.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not strange for martial artists to eat meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.89,0:40:11.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no simple way to catch animals quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.14,0:40:15.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When you really want to eat them, you have to set a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.32,0:40:23.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm an idiot, so I laid one right next to the house, and accidentally caught Nee-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.57,0:40:25.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I got in big trouble for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.65,0:40:29.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned that traps are to catch your prey,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.24,0:40:33.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,so you shouldn't set them around your house.{old: The lesson I learned is that you can't set traps near your own house.}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.08,0:40:35.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.67,0:40:37.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not surrendering, then—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.63,0:40:39.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,One thing comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.01,0:40:42.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking about it the whole time —
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.09,0:40:45.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,a way to get out of Sentou Meguri.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.26,0:40:47.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.39,0:40:49.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentou Meguri is invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.56,0:40:51.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentouryuu is the art of absolute defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.27,0:40:57.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we test out whether Kyotouryuu is really inferior to Sentouryuu!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.55,0:40:59.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.46,0:41:18.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, no traps over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.92,0:41:24.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides me, you had to look out for Togame too. {check. basically they had to be careful not to set up traps where Togame would see what they were doing}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.35,0:41:43.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you did manage to take Sentou, have you even thought of a way to transport it back to Owari?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.44,0:41:51.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I lose this fight, the shrine maidens could help you get back to Owari.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.33,0:41:52.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.40,0:41:54.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And in exchange for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.96,0:42:00.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to request that you obtain a guarantee from the Shogunate of the future of those girls and the Sanzu shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.75,0:42:02.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what do you think you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.60,0:42:04.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who my successor is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.38,0:42:09.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that she hasn't completely recovered yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.22,0:42:15.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please get the Shogunate to send someone who's kind and knows their way around people's hearts to take care of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.44,0:42:21.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even amidst the demons of the Shogunate, there must be one who fits that profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.52,0:42:23.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you acknowledging your defeat?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.35,0:42:24.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.40,0:42:28.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I can't afford to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.41,0:42:30.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to protect those girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.24,0:42:39.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just being contradictory here, but I figure it's fine if I lose this fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.79,0:42:44.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wrong to think I could save those girls with the poison of the swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.34,0:42:46.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always thought that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.38,0:42:52.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I used the sword as a cure, but if they become unable to part with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.68,0:42:55.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,in the end it'll be more poison than cure.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.56,0:42:57.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I've been waiting,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.68,0:43:03.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,waiting for people like you two to come and smash my pointless hopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.39,0:43:08.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm not admitting defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.91,0:43:29.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the original Sentou Tsurugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.13,0:43:31.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.47,0:43:35.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Togame told me the swords house souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.96,0:43:38.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The swords choose their masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.43,0:43:40.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, they don't choose who to slay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.93,0:43:45.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentou Tsurugi chose you, just like I chose Togame.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.69,0:43:47.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.70,0:43:56.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the Kyotouryuu 7th generation head, Yasuri Shichika.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.13,0:43:56.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Come!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.29,0:43:59.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And I am Izumo Daisen Sanzu's...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.51,0:44:00.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.62,0:44:04.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sentouryuu 12th generation head, Tsuruga Meisai.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.29,0:44:05.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.42,0:44:07.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I will show you the thousand secrets of Sentouryuu!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.95,0:44:08.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.80,0:44:13.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, by that point you'll be torn into pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.94,0:44:28.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuuchuu Ittou: Okumoji Kiri!{Note: Midair blade, a hundred million cuts}{check the number of zeros lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.10,0:44:31.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyotouryuu: Kyouka Suigetsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.89,0:45:05.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Togame! I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.85,0:45:09.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, it was a clear victory.{check  er.. 誤審 is like an umpire giving the wrong judgement for example}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.86,0:45:10.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.53,0:45:17.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shichika, you didn't have to...{kill her}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.83,0:45:19.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.21,0:45:27.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.18,0:45:39.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would come to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.85,0:45:49.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I will definitely obtain a guarantee of safety for this shrine and its thousand maidens from the Shogunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.73,0:45:51.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.23,0:45:55.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to happen to this shrine now?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.53,0:45:59.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no more swords so they're unarmed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.82,0:46:00.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.99,0:46:06.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, it just means things returned to how they were before the sword got involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.62,0:46:10.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai should have just done that from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.34,0:46:13.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Meisai bore one of the Deviant Blades.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.96,0:46:17.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She would have been consumed by the poison of Shikizaki's sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.05,0:46:21.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt she'd have been able to let go of it unless it was forcefully taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.64,0:46:24.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.93,0:46:30.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had lost, would you have handed over Kanna and Namakura as agreed?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.36,0:46:35.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mumble mumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.94,0:46:37.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mumble mumble?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.07,0:46:39.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.28,0:46:42.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I never once thought you could lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.82,0:46:43.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.66,0:46:45.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.92,0:46:51.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to say goodbye to these steps too...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.17,0:46:52.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to miss them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.71,0:46:55.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll miss the steps rather than the shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.63,0:46:57.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.08,0:47:02.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I just doubt I'll get the chance to embrace you like this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.31,0:47:05.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerio!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.19,0:47:20.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, they never dreamed that Japan's strongest swordsman and the owner of Hakutou Hari —
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.94,0:47:26.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sabi Hakuhei — awaited them at their destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.16,0:47:30.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How will the duel between Sabi Hakuhei and Yasuri Shichika turn out?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.96,0:47:36.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The story of Katanagatari on this month and this evening ends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.59,0:49:12.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}The strongest swordsman in Japan — Sabi Hakuhei.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.64,0:49:15.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}However powerful Shichika's Kyotouryuu is,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.35,0:49:17.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}we can't let our guard down this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.18,0:49:21.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}No, this is isn't even a question of letting down our guard or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.86,0:49:23.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}We leave to collect our 4th sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.90,0:49:26.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}The most dangerous moment for Yasuri Shichika!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.35,0:49:28.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}The most daring scheme for Togame!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.62,0:49:31.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}History will be made on the holy island of Ganryuujima!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.91,0:49:33.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}...I hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.29,0:49:36.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,714)}Next on Katanagatari: Hakutou Hari
